answerTexts: The pollen-producing reproductive organ of a flower, usually consisting of a filament and an anther.
One of the often brightly colored parts of a flower immediately surrounding the reproductive organs; a division of the corolla.
One of the separate, usually green parts forming the calyx of a flower.
Botany The expanded tip of a flower stalk or axis that bears the floral organs or the group of flowers in a head.
